article.headline: Brace hits buzzer-beater, Northeastern knocks off Charleston

images.name: Northeastern wins on baseline buzzer-beater
images.caption: Bolden Brace catches an air ball and quickly puts up a shot before the buzzer sounds to give Northeastern a 73-72 win over College of Charleston.

article.linkText: Brace hits buzzer-beater, Northeastern knocks off Charleston
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Bolden Brace hit a baseline buzzer-beating jump shot to give Northeastern a 73-72 upset win over College of Charleston on Thursday night. T.J. Williams missed a jump shot with three seconds left. Brace came away with the offensive rebound and fired off a shot just before the clock ran out. Alex Murphy had 19 points and eight rebounds for Northeastern (14-11, 7-6 CAA). Devon Begley had all 16 of his points in the second half, hitting 4 of 6 from distance. Anthony Green added 15 with 10 boards and Williams had 14 points for the Huskies. Joe Chealey had 28 points and Grant Riller added 19 for Charleston (19-7, 10-3), which had been tied for first place in the conference. Northeastern had a 17-5 run to go ahead 63-56 with 4:59 left. The Cougars clawed back to take a 72-71 lead following Nick Harris jumper with 22 seconds left.
